gegl-server: Image processing server based on GEGL

Installing
==========
npm install https://github.com/jonnor/gegl-server

Usage
=====

 # Example 1: Start the server, process an image and open it
 node server.js
 export image_url=`curl http://localhost:8888/process -d "graphData=<gegl> <gegl:crop width='512' height='512'/> <gegl:text size='80' color='black'><params> <param name='string'>GEGL SERVER</param> </params> </gegl:text> </gegl>&outputFile=myfile2.png"`
 xdg-open $image_url

 # Example 2: Embedd and use in a node.js web application
 see ./demo.js

Dependencies
=============
* GEGL: http://www.gegl.org
* node.js: http://www.nodejs.org
* node-static: https://github.com/cloudhead/node-static

